rComments: This guy is a beast, his assignments are very long but they're fantastic preparation for his midterm and for the final exam so it's really worth it. For ITI 1100 I honestly think he's the best prof available to take. The course itself is fairly easy as long as you don't fall behind and make sure you stay organized throughout the semester.

By nature, the digital systems class is a little dry and a little repetitive at times. However, this prof is the best one you can get for this class. He goes through examples clearly in class, accepts questions from the class, and makes sure you actually understand one thing before moving onto the next. Slides are also posted online for you.
